"{\"correct\": \"no\", \"explanation\": \"The use of apply with groupby in this context is incorrect because the result of apply is a Series with a different index than the original DataFrame. This will lead to misalignment when trying to assign it back to df['z']. Instead, the calculation should be done in a way that maintains the original DataFrame's index.\", \"patch\": \"9c9\\n< df['z'] = df.groupby(['y']).apply(lambda x: (x['x1'] != x['x1'].shift(-1)) | (x['x2'] != x['x2'].shift(-1))).reset_index(drop=True)\\n---\\n> df['z'] = df.groupby(['y']).transform(lambda x: (x['x1'] != x['x1'].shift(-1)) | (x['x2'] != x['x2'].shift(-1)))\"}"